4.1. Simulation for attitude controller comparison
The three controllers â€“ Feedback linearization with PD controller (FBL+ PD), Feedback linearization with LQR (FBL+LQR), and PID controller are implemented as separate Simulink models and simulated. The Simulink block layout is shown in Appendices A3- A6. A simulation time of 50s with a variable step size is given, and Ode-45 Dormand-Prince method is used to solve the numerical problem.

4.1.1. Attitude commands
The attitude commands are provided from a block, which contains step functions for each of the attitude variables. The step function starts with the initial condition as shown in Table 2, and falls to 0 with a step time of 5s for the 3 angles and rises to 3 with the same step time for height command.

